Note 1: Callsign Scottish Control will be used when Control service is being provided, otherwise callsign Scottish Information will be used. Traffic flying within or beneath the Scottish TMA requiring FIS should call Scottish Information. Note 2: FIS boundaries do not coincide with FIR boundaries. Note 3: FIS sectors are depicted at ENR 6-33. Note 4: Aircraft in the Shetland area experiencing difficulty with Scottish FIS may call Sumburgh Approach on 131.300 MHz during its hours of operation. Note 5: Frequencies may not be available H24 at all levels in all relevant sectors, see ENR 6-33. Note 6: Available at or below FL 55. Outside of these hours, if contact cannot be established on the nominated frequency for Area H (see ENR 6-33) then contact 119.875 MHz which is monitored H24.

To operate UAS within this area, UAS operators are required to notify NATS via the NATS Non-Standard Flight (NSF) Portal. UAS operators are required to notify NATS at least 14 days before the date of each activity.
